cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a deep neural network for predicting future frames in natural video sequences by decomposing motion and content. The paper uses Encoder-Decoder Convolutional Neural Network and Convolutional LSTM for pixel-level prediction, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning (cs.CV, cs.LG). The paper also discusses end-to-end training and learning to decompose motion and content without separate training, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed network architecture on human activity videos, which is a common application of multimedia (cs.MM).
